  "text": "In the current study, we showed that linseed-enriched diet up-regulated the expression of genes (SLC20A1, TRAF3IP2, TP53INP1, TNFRSF12A, TLR9 and BIRC2) which involved in IκB inhibition in porcine skeletal muscle, and might lead to decrease NF-κB activation (Table 5 ). Recent studies indicated that activation of NF-κB is inhibited by n-3 PUFAs in lymphomonocyte [CITATION_1] , and the decreased IKK activation is likely to contribute to the suppressed NF-κB activation [CITATION_2] . Our results provided an alternative explanation why n-3 PUFAs could suppress NF-κB activation.",
